Package: RIPoL
Type: Package
Title: Tree-Aware Label Propagation for Microbiome Decontamination
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Zixu",
           family = "Hao",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "your_email@georgetown.edu")
Description: 
    Implements RIPoL (Robust Inference via Phylogeny-aware Label Propagation),
    a tree-aware framework for identifying core, intermediate, and transient
    taxa in microbiome studies. The method jointly models abundance-based
    co-enrichment and prevalence-based co-existence using host?Ctaxon bipartite
    graphs and phylogenetic kernel smoothing. RIPoL supports inverse probability
    weighting to adjust for confounding and provides principled decontamination
    via joint significance in weighted and unweighted propagation spaces.
